This paper discusses the application of evolutionary algorithms (EAs) to tackle noisy optimization problems, which falls under the category of optimization and control (cs.NE). The paper also introduces a new noise handling strategy called median sampling, which involves statistical analysis and could be categorized under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the comparison between mean sampling and median sampling, which could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data mining (cs.DM).
